quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  11,72,"She said, “Oh woe to me – will I bear a child whereas I am an old woman, and this my husband, is an old man? This is something really extraordinary.”"
  11,73,"The angels said, “Do you wonder at the command of Allah? Allah’s mercy and His blessings be upon you, O people of this house; indeed He only is Most Praiseworthy, Most Honourable.”"
  11,74,"And when Ibrahim’s fear abated and the glad tidings reached him, he argued with Us regarding the people of Lut."
  11,75,"Indeed Ibrahim is most forbearing, very soft hearted, penitent."
  11,76,"“O Ibrahim, turn away from this; indeed your Lord’s command has come; and indeed a punishment will come upon them, which will not be averted.”"
  11,77,"And when Our angels came to Lut, he was distressed for them and was disheartened due to them, and said, “This is a day of great hardship.”"
  11,78,"And his people came running towards him; and they were in the habit of committing evil deeds; he said, “O my people! These women of the tribe are my daughters* – they are purer for you – therefore fear Allah and do not disgrace me in the midst of my guests; is there not even a single righteous man among you?” (* The wives of those people.)"
  11,79,"They said, “You know that we have no right to the daughters of your tribe; and you obviously know what we desire.”"
  11,80,"He said, “If only I had the strength against you or were able to get the refuge of some strong support!”"
  11,81,"The angels said, “O Lut! We are the sent ones of your Lord – they cannot get to you, therefore during the night take your entire household with you – and not one of you may turn around and see – except your wife*; she too will be afflicted with the same as they will be; indeed their promise is at morn; is not the morning imminent?” (* She was a disbeliever and sided with the culprits.)"
